<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idf68d9af9-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s10907"><num value="10907">§ 10907.</num><heading> Permission to make complaint</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="idf68d9afa-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s10907/a"><num value="a">(a)</num><content> A master may not refuse to permit, deny the opportunity to, or hinder a seaman who wishes to make a complaint authorized by this chapter.</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0" id="idf68d9afb-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s10907/b"><num value="b">(b)</num><content> A master violating this section is liable to the United States Government for civil penalty of $500.</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="idf68d9afc-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5">(<ref href="/us/pl/98/89">Pub. L. 98–89</ref>, <date date="1983-08-26">Aug. 26, 1983</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/97/577">97 Stat. 577</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
